DTSTAMP:20260413T004138Z
DTSTART:20260417T180000Z
DESCRIPTION:Friday\, April 17\, 2026\, 11am - 12pm\n\nJoin us to learn abou
	t the current state of AI capabilities and the forecast for the next 36 mo
	nths.\n\nThis event will be interpreted live in\n\nCantonese\n\nand\n\nMan
	darin.\n\n---------------------------------------------------------\n\n加入我
	們來了解人工智慧的現況以及對未來36個月的預測。\n\n本次活動將提供粵語和國語的現場傳譯。\n\n------------------------
	---------------------------------\n\n加入我们来了解人工智能的现况以及对未来36个月的预测。\n\n本次活动将提
	供粤语和普通话的现场传译。\n\nLocation Link: non-library location\n\nRegistration Requi
	red: Registration is not required. / 注册不是必须的。/ 註冊不是必須的。\n\nDetailed Descri
	ption: Anyone! Older adults who live in Central Seattle are especially enc
	ouraged to come.\, Thanks to our partner\n\nAge Friendly Seattle. \,\n\n--
	-------------------------------------------------------\, 所有人！特別鼓勵居住在西雅圖中區
	的老年人參加。\,\n\n---------------------------------------------------------\, 所
	有人！特别鼓励居住在西雅图中区的老年人参加。\n\nEvent Logistics: Join usvirtuallyonline or by ph
	one.Click\n\nhere\n\nfor more info about the event.\, Location / 地點 / 地点: 
	Chinese Information and Service Center:\n\n611 S Lane St\, Seattle\, WA 98
	104 \, ---------------------------------------------------------歡迎透過線上或電話方
	式參與活動。點擊  此處 獲取更多活動資訊。\,\n\n----------------------------------------------
	-----------欢迎通过线上或电话方式参与活动。点击  此处 获取更多活动详情。\n\nContact Us: Contact\n\nagef
	riendly@seattle.gov\n\nwith any questions.\,\n\n--------------------------
	-------------------------------\, 有疑問？發送電郵至\n\nagefriendly@seattle.gov \,\
	n\n---------------------------------------------------------\, 有疑问？发送电邮至\n
	\nagefriendly@seattle.gov\n\nADA Accommodations: We can provide accommodat
	ions for people with disabilities at Library events. Please\n\ncontactLEAP
	\n\nat least seven days before the event to request accommodations.\, All 
	Library programs are free and open to the public.-------------------------
